  "text": "Purified 12CA5 monoclonal antibodies directed at the HA epitope [CITATION_1] (the YPYDVPDY epitope of influenza virus haemagglutinin) were purchased from Berkeley Antibody (Richmond, CA, U.S.A.). The hybridoma producing 9E10 monoclonal antibody against the Myc epitope [CITATION_2] (the MASMEQK-LISEEDLNN epitope of the c-Myc protein) was obtained from the A. T. C. C. (Manassas, VA, U.S.A.). Cells were used to produce ascites in mice and antibodies were partially purified by ammonium sulphate precipitation.",
